    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <section id="getting-started" class="help-section">
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      
      <h3>Creating an Account</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Click the <strong>"Register"</strong> button in the top navigation</li>
        <li>Fill in your username, email, and password</li>
        <li>Username must be 3-50 characters, alphanumeric only</li>
        <li>Password must be at least 8 characters</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Sign Up"</strong> to create your account</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Logging In</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Click the <strong>"Login"</strong> button</li>
        <li>Enter your username and password</li>
        <li>Optionally check "Remember Me" to stay logged in</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Log In"</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <div class="help-tip">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Keep your password secure and never share it with anyone. If you forget your password, contact an administrator.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Creating Content -->
    <section id="creating-content" class="help-section">
      <h2>Creating Content</h2>

      <h3>Starting a New Thread</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Navigate to the category where you want to post</li>
        <li>Click the <strong>"New Thread"</strong> button</li>
        <li>Enter a descriptive title (up to 255 characters)</li>
        <li>Write your post content (up to 10,000 characters)</li>
        <li>Add tags to help others find your thread (optional)</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Create Thread"</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Replying to Threads</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the thread you want to reply to</li>
        <li>Scroll to the bottom of the page</li>
        <li>Type your response in the reply box</li>
        <li>Use the formatting toolbar if needed</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Post Reply"</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Editing Your Posts</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Find your post in a thread</li>
        <li>Click the <strong>"Edit"</strong> button</li>
        <li>Make your changes</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Save Changes"</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <div class="help-warning">
        <strong>Note:</strong> You can only edit your own posts. Edited posts show an "Edited" timestamp.
      </div>

      <h3>Deleting Posts</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Find your post in a thread</li>
        <li>Click the <strong>"Delete"</strong> button</li>
        <li>Confirm deletion in the popup</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="help-warning">
        <strong>Warning:</strong> Deleted posts cannot be recovered. Only moderators and admins can delete other users' posts.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Formatting -->
    <section id="formatting" class="help-section">
      <h2>Formatting Posts</h2>

      <p>Educard supports Markdown formatting for rich text posts. Here are common formatting options:</p>

      <div class="formatting-guide">
        <h3>Text Formatting</h3>
        <table class="formatting-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>You Type</th>
              <th>You Get</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>**bold text**</code></td>
              <td><strong>bold text</strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>*italic text*</code></td>
              <td><em>italic text</em></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>~~strikethrough~~</code></td>
              <td><del>strikethrough</del></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>`inline code`</code></td>
              <td><code>inline code</code></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Links</h3>
        <table class="formatting-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>[Link Text](https://example.com)</code></td>
              <td><a href="#">Link Text</a></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Headers</h3>
        <pre><code># Heading 1
## Heading 2
### Heading 3</code></pre>

        <h3>Lists</h3>
        <p><strong>Unordered List:</strong></p>
        <pre><code>- Item 1
- Item 2
- Item 3</code></pre>

        <p><strong>Ordered List:</strong></p>
        <pre><code>1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item</code></pre>

        <h3>Code Blocks</h3>
        <p>Use triple backticks for code blocks with syntax highlighting:</p>
        <pre><code>```javascript
function hello() {
  console.log("Hello, World!");
}
```</code></pre>

        <h3>Blockquotes</h3>
        <pre><code>&gt; This is a quote
&gt; It can span multiple lines</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="help-tip">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Use the "Preview" button to see how your formatted post will look before posting.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Interactions -->
    <section id="interactions" class="help-section">
      <h2>Interactions</h2>

      <h3>Voting</h3>
      <p>Upvote helpful posts or downvote unhelpful ones:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Upvote:</strong> Click the up arrow (â–²) to show appreciation</li>
        <li><strong>Downvote:</strong> Click the down arrow (â–¼) for off-topic or unhelpful posts</li>
        <li>You can change your vote or remove it by clicking again</li>
        <li>You cannot vote on your own posts</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Bookmarking</h3>
      <p>Save threads for later reading:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Click the <strong>"Bookmark"</strong> button on any thread</li>
        <li>View your bookmarks from your profile</li>
        <li>Remove bookmarks by clicking the button again</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Notifications</h3>
      <p>Get notified about activity:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>New replies to your threads</li>
        <li>Mentions of your username</li>
        <li>Upvotes on your posts</li>
        <li>Click the bell icon (ðŸ””) to view notifications</li>
        <li>Unread notifications show a badge count</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Reporting Content</h3>
      <p>Report inappropriate content to moderators:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Click the <strong>"Report"</strong> button on the post</li>
        <li>Select a reason (spam, harassment, off-topic, etc.)</li>
        <li>Optionally add details</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Submit Report"</strong></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- Profile -->
    <section id="profile" class="help-section">
      <h2>Your Profile</h2>

      <h3>Viewing Your Profile</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Click your username in the top navigation</li>
        <li>Or visit <code>/users/your-username</code></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Editing Your Profile</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to your profile page</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Edit Profile"</strong></li>
        <li>Update your display name, bio, or avatar</li>
        <li>Click <strong>"Save Changes"</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Profile Information</h3>
      <p>Your profile shows:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Username and display name</li>
        <li>Join date</li>
        <li>Biography (optional)</li>
        <li>Post count and reputation</li>
        <li>Recent threads and posts</li>
        <li>Bookmarked threads</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Search -->
    <section id="search" class="help-section">
      <h2>Search & Discovery</h2>

      <h3>Searching Content</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Click the search icon or use the search box in navigation</li>
        <li>Enter keywords to search</li>
        <li>Filter by type: Threads, Posts, Users, or Tags</li>
        <li>Results highlight matching terms</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Using Tags</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Tags help categorize and find content</li>
        <li>Click any tag to see related threads</li>
        <li>Add relevant tags when creating threads</li>
        <li>Popular tags appear in the sidebar</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Browsing Categories</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>All categories are listed on the homepage</li>
        <li>Click a category to see its threads</li>
        <li>Threads are sorted by recent activity</li>
        <li>Pinned threads appear at the top</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Guidelines -->
    <section id="guidelines" class="help-section">
      <h2>Community Guidelines</h2>

      <h3>Be Respectful</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Treat others with kindness and respect</li>
        <li>No personal attacks, harassment, or bullying</li>
        <li>Respect different opinions and perspectives</li>
        <li>Keep discussions civil and constructive</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Stay On Topic</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Post in relevant categories</li>
        <li>Keep replies related to the thread topic</li>
        <li>Avoid derailing conversations</li>
        <li>Start a new thread for new topics</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Quality Content</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Write clear, well-thought-out posts</li>
        <li>Use proper grammar and spelling</li>
        <li>Provide context and details</li>
        <li>Search before posting to avoid duplicates</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Prohibited Content</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Spam or excessive self-promotion</li>
        <li>Illegal content or activities</li>
        <li>Hate speech or discrimination</li>
        <li>Personal information of others</li>
        <li>Explicit or inappropriate content</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="help-warning">
        <strong>Violations may result in:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>Post or thread deletion</li>
          <li>Temporary suspension</li>
          <li>Permanent ban from the forum</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section id="faq" class="help-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I change my password?</h3>
        <p>Currently, password changes are not available through the interface. Please contact an administrator if you need to reset your password.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I delete my account?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Contact an administrator to request account deletion. Note that your posts may remain visible with "[deleted]" as the author.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Why can't I post in certain threads?</h3>
        <p>Threads can be locked by moderators to prevent further replies. Locked threads show a lock icon (ðŸ”’).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I become a moderator?</h3>
        <p>Moderators are selected by administrators based on community participation and trustworthiness. There is no application process.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I use HTML in posts?</h3>
        <p>No, HTML is not allowed for security reasons. Use Markdown formatting instead.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What file types can I upload?</h3>
        <p>Currently, image uploads are supported (JPG, PNG, GIF). Maximum file size is 5 MB.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How is post ordering determined?</h3>
        <p>Posts within threads are ordered chronologically (oldest first). Thread listing can be sorted by recent activity or creation date.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I edit my post after submitting?</h3>
        <p>Yes, use the "Edit" button on your post. An "Edited" timestamp will appear to show the post was modified.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does "pinned" mean?</h3>
        <p>Pinned threads stay at the top of the category listing. Only moderators and admins can pin threads.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I contact moderators?</h3>
        <p>Use the "Report" feature on any post, or post in the "Site Feedback" category if available.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section id="contact" class="help-section">
      <h2>Still Need Help?</h2>
      <p>If you couldn't find the answer to your question:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Search the forum for similar questions</li>
        <li>Post in the "Site Help" or "Feedback" category</li>
        <li>Contact an administrator directly</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
